<subSubSection id="C37642ECFFFFFFCAFADF543B5F4AF997" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="18" pageNumber="570" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD31167FFFFFFCAFADF543B5F10FE18" blockId="18.[1378,2584,2933,3204]" lastBlockId="19.[803,1396,284,711]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="18" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B918CD75FFFFFFCBFADF543B5C3EF3C7" bold="true" box="[1379,1631,3122,3155]" pageId="18" pageNumber="570">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 165-275 mm, tail 118-231 mm; weight 160-400 g. Simons’s Spiny-rat is relatively large, with very characteristic elongated body, long and narrow face, long ears, absolutely and proportionately long tail (¢.85% of headbody length), and long narrow hindfeet.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1341EFFFFFFFCBFFD754DE5BD9F218" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6624579" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6624579" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6624579/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="570" startId="18.[107,137,3287,3312]" targetBox="[11,2751,12,3642]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph id="8BD31167FFFFFFCBFFD754DE5BD9F218" blockId="18.[105,2568,3287,3473]" pageId="18" pageNumber="570">
